'''Meta Tracker''' is a [[desktop search|search system]] for [[Linux]] and other [[Unix-like]] systems. Meta Tracker is written in the [[C (programming language)|C]] programming language.
[[Nautilus (file manager)|Nautilus]] has support for both Tracker and [[Beagle (software)|Beagle]].
One of the developers of the [[Conduit (software)|Conduit]] application has suggested using MetaTracker to create "a metadata-enabled [[GNOME]]"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.johnstowers.co.nz/blog/index.php/2007/02/06/a-metadata-enabled-gnome/ |title=A Metadata Enabled GNOME - Johns Blog |author=John Stowers |accessdate=2009-08-27 }}</ref>, which would be similar to using [[Strigi]] as an indexer for a metadata framework in [[KDE Software Compilation 4]].
